HEADWORD: Raffia palm
<hw>Raf"fi*a palm</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧f"f⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧ p⟦aum⟧m`)</pr>.
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A pinnate-leaved palm (<spn>Raphia ruffia</spn>)
native of Madagascar, and of considerable economic importance on account
of the strong fiber (raffia) obtained from its leafstalks.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The jupati palm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Raffinose</ent>⟦br⟧
